[2026-07-01T08:14:02.362Z] [INFO] [stderr] +### 16.1 `@ielts/storage/syncService`
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.362Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.362Z] [INFO] [stderr] +The sync service lives at `packages/storage/src/syncService.ts` and provides a framework-agnostic API for data export, import, sync tracking, and bridge communication.
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.362Z] [INFO] [stderr] -## 16. Summary
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.362Z] [INFO] [stderr] +**Key exports:**
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.362Z] [INFO] [stderr]  
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.362Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.362Z] [INFO] [stderr] +++ /Users/phamthanhhung/Desktop/MyProject/IELTS/docs/extension-architecture.md
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.362Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.362Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.362Z] [INFO] [stderr] +**Design approach:** Rather than importing extension or website modules directly, the sync service uses **dependency injection** — callers provide `StorageHandlers` (getter/saver/deleter functions for each entity type) and `StorageGet`/`StorageSet` for `chrome.storage` operations. This keeps the package reusable and testable.
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.362Z] [INFO] [stderr] +## 16. Sync Service Implementation
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.362Z] [INFO] [stderr] +|--------|---------|
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.362Z] [INFO] [stderr] +| `exportExtensionData(handlers)` | Reads all extension stores → `ExtensionExportData` JSON |
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.362Z] [INFO] [stderr] +| `getSyncStatus(storageGet)` | Reads pending sync items from `chrome.storage.local` |
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.362Z] [INFO] [stderr] +| `importExtensionData(data, handlers, mode)` | Writes `ExtensionExportData` into extension stores with merge/replace |
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.362Z] [INFO] [stderr] +| Export | Purpose |
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.362Z] [INFO] [stderr] +| `markItemPending(id, type, get, set)` | Adds an item to the pending sync queue |
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.362Z] [INFO] [stderr] +| `downloadJson(data, filename)` | Triggers a browser file download |
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.362Z] [INFO] [stderr] +| `validateExtensionExportData(data)` | Zod schema validation for backup files |
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.362Z] [INFO] [stderr] +| `readJsonFile(file)` | Reads and parses a JSON `File` object |
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.362Z] [INFO] [stderr] +| `isValidBridgeMessage(data)` | Type guard for incoming bridge messages |
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.362Z] [INFO] [stderr] +| `markItemsSynced(ids, get, set)` | Removes items from pending queue after successful sync |
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.362Z] [INFO] [stderr] +| `createBridgeMessage(action, data)` | Creates a typed bridge message for `postMessage` |
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.362Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.362Z] [INFO] [stderr] +```typescript
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.362Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.362Z] [INFO] [stderr] +### 16.2 Extension Export Format (`ExtensionExportData`)
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.362Z] [INFO] [stderr] +  meta: {
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.362Z] [INFO] [stderr] +    version: number
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.362Z] [INFO] [stderr] +    exportedAt: string
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.362Z] [INFO] [stderr] +interface ExtensionExportData {
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.362Z] [INFO] [stderr] +    source: 'extension' | 'website'
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.362Z] [INFO] [stderr] +  mistakes: Record<string, unknown>[]          // from mistakeStore.ts
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.362Z] [INFO] [stderr] +  vocabulary: Record<string, unknown>[]       // from vocabularyStore.ts
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.362Z] [INFO] [stderr] +    appVersion: string
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.362Z] [INFO] [stderr] +  }
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.362Z] [INFO] [stderr] +  learningEntries: Record<string, unknown>[]  // from indexedDB.ts
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr] +}
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.362Z] [INFO] [stderr] +  videos: Record<string, unknown>[]            // from videoStore.ts
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr] +The format is extension-specific but convertible to the website's `AppExportData` format via the mapper functions in `syncService.ts`.
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr] +```
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.362Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr] +| `replace` | Clears all existing data in each store before importing |
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.362Z] [INFO] [stderr] +  articles: Record<string, unknown>[]          // from articleStore.ts
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr] +### 16.3 Import Modes
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr] +The user chooses the mode in the Backup & Restore UI before uploading a backup file.
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr] +| Mode | Behavior |
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr] +| `merge` | Adds new items, keeps existing items with same ID unchanged |
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr] +```
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr] +|------|----------|
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr] +When the IELTS Journey website is open, the content script injects a bridge that communicates via `window.postMessage`. The protocol is request-response with `requestId` correlation:
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr] +```
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr] +Extension → Page: { source: "ielts-extension", action: "SYNC_REQUEST", requestId: "abc" }
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr] +### 16.4 Bridge Protocol (Real-time Sync)
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr] +Page → Extension: { source: "ielts-page", action: "SYNC_RESPONSE", data: {...}, requestId: "abc" }
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr] +The bridge is defined in `packages/storage/src/syncService.ts` with `BridgeMessage` and `BridgeResponse` types. The actual injection and message routing is handled by content scripts.
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr] +### 16.5 Browser Limitations
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr] +| Limitation | Impact | Mitigation |
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr] +| Service worker lifetime is limited (MV3) | Background sync cannot run indefinitely | Sync happens on-demand or when the user visits the website; no background polling |
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr] +| IndexedDB is **origin-bound** | Extension origin (`chrome-extension://`) and website origin (`http://localhost:5173` or production domain) cannot share the same IndexedDB database | Each maintains its own database; sync is via JSON export/import or bridge when website is open |
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr] +| `chrome.storage` is extension-scoped | Website cannot read `chrome.storage.local` | Bridge uses `window.postMessage` for cross-origin communication |
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr] +---
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr] +## 17. Summary
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr] +| Content scripts run in an **isolated world** | Cannot directly access website's IndexedDB | Bridge script is injected into the page's main world via script element |
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr] +|------------|--------|------------|
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr] +| `window.postMessage` requires the website tab to be open | Bridge sync is unavailable when website is closed | Fall back to manual export/import |
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr]  |-----------------------|-------------------------------------------------------|
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr]  | Aspect                | Decision                                              |
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr]  | Manifest              | V3                                                    |
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr]  | AI                    | User's own API key, called from service worker via fetch |
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr]  | Styling               | Tailwind CSS 3 (shared theme tokens with website)     |
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr]  | Storage               | IndexedDB (primary) + chrome.storage.local (settings/cache) |
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr]  | UI Framework          | React 18 + TypeScript + Vite                          |
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr] -| Backup                | JSON export/import (same format as website)           |
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr] +| Backup                | JSON export/import (shared `ExtensionExportData` format) |
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr]  | Content script world  | ISOLATED (MV3 default)                                |
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr]  | Permissions           | Minimal: activeTab, contextMenus, storage, alarms    |
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr]  | Monorepo              | pnpm workspace with shared packages                   |
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr] [0m
[2026-07-01T08:14:02.363Z] [INFO] [stderr]  | Sync with website     | Hybrid: extension-scoped IndexedDB + optional bridge via postMessage |
